
# 📘 01 – Java Basics

This file covers the core basics of Java necessary to start your journey in programming and Data Structures & Algorithms (DSA).

---

## 🧠 1. Hello World in Java

```java
public class Main {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        System.out.println("Hello, World!");
    }
}


---

📌 2. Java Data Types

Data Type	Example	Size

int	10	4 bytes
float	10.5f	4 bytes
double	10.5	8 bytes
char	'A'	2 bytes
boolean	true / false	1 bit
String	"Hello"	—



---

✍️ 3. Variables & Constants

int age = 25;
float pi = 3.14f;
final int MAX = 100; // Constant


---

📥 4. Input in Java (Using Scanner)

import java.util.Scanner;

public class Main {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        Scanner sc = new Scanner(System.in);
        int num = sc.nextInt();
        System.out.println("You entered: " + num);
    }
}


---

⚙️ 5. Operators

Arithmetic: +, -, *, /, %

Relational: ==, !=, <, >, <=, >=

Logical: &&, ||, !



---

🔁 6. Conditionals

if-else Example:

int age = 20;
if(age >= 18) {
    System.out.println("Adult");
} else {
    System.out.println("Not Adult");
}

switch Example:

int day = 2;
switch(day) {
    case 1: System.out.println("Mon"); break;
    case 2: System.out.println("Tue"); break;
    default: System.out.println("Other day");
}


---

🔄 7. Loops in Java

for loop:

for(int i = 0; i < 5; i++) {
    System.out.println(i);
}

while loop:

int i = 0;
while(i < 5) {
    System.out.println(i);
    i++;
}

do-while loop:

int i = 0;
do {
    System.out.println(i);
    i++;
} while(i < 5);


---

🧮 8. Arrays

int[] arr = new int[5]; // Declaration
arr[0] = 10;            // Assignment

for(int i = 0; i < arr.length; i++) {
    System.out.println(arr[i]);
}


---

📘 9. Basic Java Code Template

import java.util.*;

public class Main {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        Scanner sc = new Scanner(System.in);
        
        // Your code here
    }
}


---

✅ Practice Tasks

1. Write a program to take 2 numbers and print their sum.


2. Write a program to check if a number is even or odd.


3. Write a program to print numbers from 1 to N using a loop.


